---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="About — Yannik Peschke" 
  description="Learn more about Yannik Peschke, Software Architect specializing in micro-frontend architectures and the Rspack ecosystem."
>

<h1>About Me</h1>

<p class="intro">
I’m a Software Architect focused on designing and scaling resilient web ecosystems. My work centers on simplifying large-scale systems, enabling team autonomy, and accelerating delivery through thoughtful architecture, custom tooling, and infrastructure.
I help teams move fast and independently using Module Federation and the evolving Rspack ecosystem—where I actively contribute and advocate. When I started my coding journey, jQuery was still the GOAT, and I still value pragmatic problem-solving over hype.

Arch Linux, Neovim, Open Source Software and building systems that don’t fight their users are my happy place.
</p>

<p>
Outside of work, I love running mountain trails, reading a good book, or channeling creativity into complex meals. I’m endlessly curious and always looking for new ways to learn and grow.
</p>

<h2>Work & Expertise</h2>

<p>
As a Software Architect, I focus on transforming highly complex monolithic web systems into dynamic, interconnected micro-frontend architectures. I lead the technical orchestration of frontends, enabling decentralized teams to collaborate efficiently across a shared customer journey.

My north star is delivering products that are performant, secure, resilient, and seamless. Beyond architecture, I own onboarding and governance practices and documentations and act as a technical mentor and consultant for developers, stakeholders, and design teams.
</p>

<p>
  When I code outside of work, it’s usually exploratory—researching ideas or refining my Neovim setup. I’m intentional about maintaining clear boundaries between work and personal time, prioritizing recovery and focus so I can consistently deliver high-quality outcomes at work.
</p>

<h2>Languages & Libraries</h2>

<div class="skills-grid">
  <div class="skill-category">
    <h3>Classic Frontend</h3>
    <p class="skill-list">
      Yes, I learned frontend when jQuery was the GOAT! Having a solid foundation on classic technology without abstraction layers is mandatory to actually understand any advanced framework or toolkit (looking at you React and Tailwind).
    </p>
    <p class="skill-list">
      HTML5, Handlebars, CSS3, Sass, Javascript, jQuery, NodeJs
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="skill-category">
    <h3>Modern Frontend</h3>
    <p class="skill-list">
      Advanced tools I work with for modern web application development with a focus on first level citizen products for micro frontend architectures.
    </p>
    <p class="skill-list">
      TypeScript, React, Modern.js, Rsbuild, Rslib, Rspress, Playwright, Rstest, Module Federation
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="skill-category">
    <h3>Bundler</h3>
    <p class="skill-list">
    It is my daily business to adapt, maintain and modernize/migrate bundlers to keep pipeline performance, frontend infrastructure and developer experience on a peak level. This also includes writing custom Rspack plugins (Rust bundler following the amazing extensible API architecture philosophy of Webpack).
    I am eternally grateful I do not have to work with Gulp, Bower or Grunt anymore.
    </p>
    <p class="skill-list">
      Rspack, Webpack
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="skill-category">
    <h3>Infra</h3>
    <p class="skill-list">
    I am not a DevOps specialist but I am familiar configuring my own docker-compose files, gitlab pipelines and reverse-proxy rules for my use-cases. For more advanced stuff I like to consult DevOps specialists - Know your focus area!
    </p>
    <p class="skill-list">
      Gitlab, Docker, Kubernetes, Traefik
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="skill-category">
    <h3>Generic</h3>
    <p class="skill-list">
      Additional tech I like to use to keep the work rolling.
    </p>
    <p class="skill-list">
      OAuth, OpenApi, Lua, Neovim, Tmux, Bash, Git
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<h2>My Dev Setup</h2>

<p>
  I'm a strong believer in a highly customized and efficient development environment. My setup is built around a few key tools that help me stay productive and focused.
</p>

<div class="skills-grid">
  <div class="skill-category">
    <h3>Operating System</h3>
    <p class="skill-list">
    My go-to setup is Arch Linux paired with a dynamic tiling compositor, to manage my windows and workspaces with ease and fast. This is especially important to stay in flow longer. Reducing finger and eye fatigue goes a long way in extensive coding sessions. 
    Unfortunately, I am currently bound to a Windows machine at work. Without WSL2 I would propably crash out 🙈
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="skill-category">
    <h3>Core Tools</h3>
    <ul class="tool-list">
      <li><strong>Neovim:</strong> My custom-built Neovim configuration is the heart of my coding workflow. I love it for the keyboard centric approach and blazingly fast motions. Also, Neovim forced me to learn how Editors and IDEs actually work.</li>
      <li><strong>Tmux:</strong> I use Tmux to manage multiple terminal sessions and windows from a single screen. Same like Neovim it pushes the keyboard centric usage of a PC to navigate around in a blink of an eye.</li>
      <li><strong>Lazygit & LazyDocker:</strong> To interact with Git and Docker from within a TUI, I rely on these two tools. They provide a simple, user interface that makes daily tasks quick and effortless without switching windows or context.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="skill-list" style="margin-top: var(--spacing-sm);">
    My entire setup is designed to be fast, keyboard-driven, and distraction-free, allowing me to fully immerse myself in the code. #IUseVimByTheWay (The ones who know will understand :-) )
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="contact-section">
  <h2 style="margin-top: 0;">Get in Touch</h2>
  <p>
  I'm always interested and proactive in connecting with other engineers or people from the tech-bubble. It is important to stay open-minded and discuss on tech-trends, complex architecture problems or just enjoying the Open Source Community 
  </p>
  <div class="contact-links">
    <a href="https://github.com/YanPes" class="contact-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>
    <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/yannik-peschke-a48012108/" class="contact-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a>
  </div>
</div>

</Layout>

<style>
.intro {
  font-size: 1.25rem;
  color: var(--text-secondary);
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);
}

.experience-grid {
  display: grid;
  gap: var(--spacing-lg);
  margin-top: var(--spacing-md);
}

.experience-item {
  padding-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
}

.experience-item:last-child {
  border-bottom: none;
}

.experience-header {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  align-items: flex-start;
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  gap: var(--spacing-xs);
}

.experience-title {
  font-family: var(--font-main);
  font-size: 1.125rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--accent);
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.05em;
}

.experience-period {
  font-family: var(--font-main);
  font-size: 14px;
  color: var(--text-tertiary);
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.05em;
}

.experience-description {
  font-size: 1rem;
  color: var(--text-secondary);
  line-height: 1.6;
}

.skills-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
  gap: var(--spacing-md);
  margin-top: var(--spacing-md);
}

.skill-category {
  padding: var(--spacing-md);
  padding-left: var(--spacing-lg);
  background-color: transparent;
  border-left: 1px solid var(--border-color);
  transition: all 0.2s ease;
  position: relative;
}

.skill-category:hover {
  border-left-color: var(--accent);
  padding-left: calc(var(--spacing-lg) + 10px);
}

.skill-category h3 {
  margin-top: 0;
  font-size: 1.125rem;
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
}

.skill-category h3::before {
  content: ">";
  margin-right: 10px;
  color: var(--accent);
  opacity: 0;
  transform: translateX(-10px);
  transition: all 0.2s ease;
}

.skill-category:hover h3::before {
  opacity: 1;
  transform: translateX(0);
}

.skill-list {
  font-size: 1rem;
  color: var(--text-secondary);
  line-height: 1.8;
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
}

.skill-list:last-of-type {
  margin-bottom: 0;
}

.balance-list {
  list-style: none;
  padding: 0;
  margin: var(--spacing-md) 0;
  color: var(--text-secondary);
}

.balance-list li {
  padding: var(--spacing-xs) 0;
  position: relative;
  padding-left: 1.5rem;
  transition: all 0.2s ease;
}

.balance-list li:hover {
  color: var(--text-primary);
  transform: translateX(5px);
}

.balance-list li::before {
  content: "*";
  position: absolute;
  left: 0;
  color: var(--text-tertiary);
  font-family: var(--font-main);
}

.balance-list li:hover::before {
  color: var(--accent);
}

.tool-list {
  list-style: none;
  padding: 0;
  margin: 0 0 var(--spacing-sm) 0;
}

.tool-list li {
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
  color: var(--text-secondary);
  line-height: 1.6;
}

.tool-list li:last-child {
  margin-bottom: 0;
}

.tool-list strong {
  color: var(--text-primary);
}

.contact-section {
  margin-top: var(--spacing-xl);
  padding: var(--spacing-lg);
  background-color: var(--bg-secondary);
  border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
}

.contact-links {
  display: flex;
  gap: var(--spacing-md);
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  margin-top: var(--spacing-md);
}

.contact-link {
  font-family: var(--font-main);
  color: var(--text-primary);
  text-decoration: none;
  padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
  border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
  transition: all 0.2s ease;
  font-weight: 700;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.05em;
}

.contact-link:hover {
  background-color: transparent;
  color: var(--accent);
  border-color: var(--accent);
  box-shadow: 0 0 15px rgba(192, 254, 4, 0.2);
}

h2:first-of-type {
  margin-top: var(--spacing-lg);
}

@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .skills-grid {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  }

  .experience-header {
    flex-direction: column;
  }
}
</style>
